text: Houyele Ba (born July 17, 1992) is a Mauritanian middle-distance runner. She competed at the 2016 Summer Olympics in the women's 800 metres race; her time of 2:43.52 in the heats did not qualify her for the semifinals. ==References== Category:1992 births Category:Living people Category:Mauritanian female middle-distance runners Category:Olympic athletes of Mauritania Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2016 Summer Olympics
